{{Trauciendu}}'''Abderrahmane Abdelli''' es un músicu, compositol i cantautol berébel conociu pol mestural el estilu tradicional ancestral la su tierra con estilus moelnus d'algotras culturas.

==Via==
[[File:Abderrahmane Abdelli.jpg|200px|thumb|right|Abdelli en direutu]]
Abdelli tuvu nacéncia en Mechta Behalil, ena Cabília [[Argélia|Argelina]], en runchándusi la Guerra la Endependéncia dessi pais. La su família hue despraçá quandu las huerças [[fráncia|francesas]] bombardearun el su pueblu, Kennour. Dispuezinu la guerra, la família d'Abdelli se estabreció ena ciá costera de Dellys, ena [[Cabília]]. En huendu entovia un zagalinu, Abdelli costruyó la su primel quitarra d'una lata vieja d'azeiti güera, una tabla maera i hilu pescal.<ref>[http://www.orientaljazz.com/Abdelli-E.htm 1 "Biography: Abdelli" GekkoBeat.com]</ref> Alú de dominal la quitarra, el maestru [[música chaabi|música ''chaabi'']] Chaïd Moh-Esguir le deprendió a tocal la mandolina.

Abdelli hizu su debut musican en Dellys, [[Cabília]], en el festival Algerian Independence de 1974.<ref>[http://users.skynet.be/sky77600/abdelli/BIOGRAPHY.htm "Abdelli Biography" Thierry Van Roy Productions]</ref>  He won several contests in [[Algeria]] for amateur singers.<ref name="Abdelli World Music Central">[http://www.worldmusiccentral.org/artists/artist_page.php?id=1175 "Abdelli" World Music Central]</ref> Abdelli produced his first album in 1984, but it saw little success. Two years later, he released an album that sold 12,000 copies, but never received payment from his record company.  Abdelli produced a couple of albums in Algeria, but moved to [[Belgium]] in 1984. It was there "he met producer Thierry Van Roy, who was so fascinated with Abdelli's music that he spent two years exploring the roots of the Berbers' musical tradition at the University of Algiers."<ref name="Abdelli World Music Central"/> Since 1986 he has made his home in [[Brussels]], Belgium.

Abdelli's most popular albums are ''New Moon''<ref> Abdelli (1995) ''New Moon'' Real World, New York, CDRW54, arranged by Thierry Van Roy, recorded by Thierry Van Roy Studios, Brussels, Belgium;</ref> and ''Among Brothers''<ref>Abdelli (2003) ''Among Brothers'' Real World Records, Virgin Music, Wiltshire, UK, arranged by Thierry Van Roy, recorded in various locations between Nov. 1998 and May 2001;</ref> He has performed at major festivals in Europe, including [[World of Music, Arts and Dance|WOMAD]] and the [[0110 concerts#Ghent|0110 concert in Ghent]]. In addition to Europe he has toured in England, the USA and Canada.

